  "prompt": "Do US presidents get bodyguard protection after they have left the office?",
  "response": "Yes, former U.S. presidents receive lifetime protection from the United States Secret Service after they leave office. This protection extends to their spouses as well. Additionally, children of former presidents are protected until they reach the age of 16. This provision was reinstated by the Former Presidents Protection Act of 2012, which reversed a previous law that limited Secret Service protection for former presidents to just 10 years after leaving office.",
